---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Container from '../components/Container.astro';
import Timeline from '../components/Timeline.astro';
import ContactForm from '../components/ContactForm.astro';
import HamburgerMenu from '../components/HamburgerMenu.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <HamburgerMenu />
  
  <Hero />

  <!-- About / Journey Start -->
  <Section id="about">
    <Container class="max-w-4xl">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-12 text-center text-nordic-mist">
          The Journey
        </h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8 text-lg text-nordic-fog leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            From the west coast of Sweden to the fjords of Norway, my path has been guided by 
            a singular obsession: <span class="text-aurora-blue font-medium">making things efficient</span>.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            What started with algorithms and data structures at Chalmers University evolved into 
            building systems that serve hundreds of millions of users. I've worked on recommendation 
            engines processing billions of requests, built traceability systems for sustainable futures, 
            and now craft seamless payment experiences.
          </p>

          <p>
            But efficiency isn't just about code. It's about <span class="text-aurora-green font-medium">understanding systems</span>—whether 
            that's distributed architecture, machine learning models, or the fermentation process 
            in a sourdough starter.
          </p>

          <div class="pt-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 text-nordic-mist">What I Do</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-fog/80">
              I build scalable systems using clean architecture, domain-driven design, and CQRS patterns. 
              I work with algorithms, AI/ML models, and recommendation engines. I think about efficiency 
              at every layer—from memory optimization to API design to developer experience.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="pt-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 text-nordic-mist">Education</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-fog/80">
              <strong class="text-nordic-mist">Master of Science in Software Engineering</strong><br />
              Chalmers University of Technology, Gothenburg<br />
              <span class="text-sm text-nordic-fog/60">Focus: Algorithms, Software Architecture, and Quality Measurements</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <!-- Timeline Section -->
  <Section id="journey" background="gray">
    <Container class="max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-16 text-center text-nordic-mist">
        The Path
      </h2>
      <div>
        <Timeline />
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <!-- Philosophy Section -->
  <Section id="philosophy">
    <Container class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="text-center space-y-8">
        <blockquote class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-serif italic text-nordic-fog/80 leading-relaxed">
          "Efficiency is not about doing more.<br class="hidden md:block" />
          It's about doing what matters, elegantly."
        </blockquote>
        
        <div class="pt-12 text-left space-y-6 text-nordic-fog">
          <p>
            Whether I'm optimizing a distributed system to handle millions of requests or 
            perfecting a sourdough recipe, the principles are the same: understand the fundamentals, 
            measure your progress, iterate relentlessly.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            I'm drawn to problems where efficiency matters—where milliseconds in latency 
            affect user experience, where memory optimization means serving more users, 
            where clean architecture enables teams to move faster.
          </p>

          <p>
            From Stockholm to Gothenburg to Oslo, I've been fortunate to work with exceptional 
            teams building state-of-the-art systems. But the journey doesn't stop. There's 
            always another algorithm to optimize, another architecture to refine, another 
            problem worth solving.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <!-- Interests -->
  <Section id="interests" background="gray">
    <Container class="max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-12 text-center text-nordic-mist">
        Beyond Code
      </h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="bg-nordic-deep/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-nordic-fog/10 rounded-lg p-8 hover:border-aurora-green/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 text-nordic-mist">Cooking</h3>
          <p class="text-nordic-fog/80 leading-relaxed">
            The kitchen is my second lab. Sourdough fermentation, Swedish classics, 
            Nordic ingredients. Each recipe is an algorithm waiting to be optimized.
            Check out my <a href="/blog" class="text-aurora-green hover:text-aurora-blue transition-colors underline">cooking blog</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-nordic-deep/30 backdrop-blur-sm border border-nordic-fog/10 rounded-lg p-8 hover:border-aurora-blue/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold mb-4 text-nordic-mist">Speaking & Sharing</h3>
          <p class="text-nordic-fog/80 leading-relaxed">
            I enjoy discussing LLMs, scalable architectures, and efficiency patterns. 
            Whether it's a conference talk or mentoring developers, sharing knowledge 
            is how we all grow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>

  <!-- Contact Section -->
  <Section id="contact">
    <Container class="max-w-4xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 text-center text-nordic-mist">
        Let's Connect
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-nordic-fog text-center mb-12">
        Whether you're looking for someone to speak at your event, collaborate on a project, 
        or just want to chat about systems architecture—I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div>
        <ContactForm />
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
